This paper discusses the ethical implications of AI and proposes a tool to ensure that AI benefits humanity. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also discusses ethical principles and codes of conduct, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.ETHICS sub-category. The paper proposes a commitment by AI firms, which involves donating profits to benefit humanity, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG sub-category. The paper also discusses the downsides of AI deployment, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CYBER sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a tool to address issues related to AI and its impact on society, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SI sub-category.
